#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is LTSP?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:33
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"LTSP is an abbreviation for \"Linux Terminal Server Project\". Installed\n"
"on a server it can supply many workstations (so called thin-clients)\n"
"with identical environments. All applications run on the server and\n"
"therefore you can use old PCs and convert them into XTerminals. This\n"
"reduces costs and maintenance especially in an environment where you\n"
"need to have an uniform workspace on each computer you login, e.g. in\n"
"schools or firms.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:47 en/ltsp.xml:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preliminaries"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"All of the examples in this document presume that your server's IP is\n"
"192.168.0.254, your domain is named yourdomain.com and your network is\n"
"192.168.0.0/24.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First of all, you must have a working Gentoo system. Please read the\n"
"Gentoo Installation Manual for your architecture on <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.gentoo.org/doc\">Gentoo's Documentation Website</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then lets begin with the easiest step, installing the ltsp package:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Emerge LTSP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge ltsp</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "This will install the following packages as dependencies:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/ltsp.xml:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "<b>XFree</b>: They are called XTerminals, guess why :)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/ltsp.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>DHCP</b>: DHCP is a protocol for automating the configuration of\n"
"    computers that use TCP/IP, used by ltsp to distribute IPs to the\n"
"    workstations.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/ltsp.xml:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>NFS</b>: NFS is a protocol to allow access to harddisks through\n"
"    the network, used by ltsp to mount a base system for the\n"
"    workstations.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/ltsp.xml:95
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>TFTP</b>: TFTP is a simple file transfer protocol, used by ltsp\n"
"    to transfer the kernel to the workstations.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/ltsp.xml:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>XINETD</b>: Xinetd is a powerful replacement for inetd, with\n"
"    advanced features, used by ltsp to start tftp.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/ltsp.xml:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have the kde/gnome useflag set, it will also install a complete kde/gnome\n"
"system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:114
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "After the emerge process has finished all services must be configured:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "System Logger"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To analyze problems easier, the system logger must be configured to\n"
"accept remote connections. Please read the documentation of your\n"
"system logger on how to achieve this. If, for example, you are using\n"
"sysklogd, all you need to do is edit <path>/etc/conf.d/sysklogd</path> and add\n"
"\"-r\" to the SYSLOGD line:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/conf.d/sysklogd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:137
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SYSLOGD=\"-m 0 -r\"\n"
"KLOGD=\"-c 3 -2\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "NFS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:148
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next step is to edit your <path>/etc/exports</path> file, in order to\n"
"allow the workstations to mount the root filesystem. There should be at\n"
"least two lines in it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/exports"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:154
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"/opt/ltsp-4.1/i386         192.168.0.0/255.255.255.0(ro,no_root_squash,async)\n"
"/var/opt/ltsp/swapfiles    192.168.0.0/255.255.255.0(rw,no_root_squash,async)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/ltsp.xml:159
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You have to alter the network/netmask to match your network/netmask\n"
"settings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:164
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now start NFS.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:167
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting nfs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>rc-update add nfs default</i>\n"
"# <i>/etc/init.d/nfs start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid "xinetd/tftp"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"TFTP requires a bit of configuring to get it to work properly. First, edit\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/in.tftpd</path> to set tftpd's options and path correctly:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/conf.d/in.tftpd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:183
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"INTFTPD_PATH=\"/tftpboot\"\n"
"INTFTPD_OPTS=\"-s ${INTFTPD_PATH}\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:188
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The -s flag specifies that TFTP is to run in secure chrooted mode\n"
"(recommended). This means that you don't need to include the\n"
"<path>/tftpboot</path> path for example in the DHCP configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next, configure xinetd to run TFTP and allow remote connections. By default\n"
"TFTP won't be started by xinetd, so edit <path>/etc/xinetd.d/tftp</path> and\n"
"replace <c>disable=yes</c> with <c>disable=no</c>. If the file is missing just\n"
"go ahead and create <path>/etc/xinetd.d/tftp</path> with the contents below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:200
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/xinetd.d/tftp"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:201
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"service tftp\n"
"{\n"
"        disable = no\n"
"        socket_type = dgram\n"
"        protocol = udp\n"
"        wait = yes\n"
"        user = root\n"
"        server = /usr/sbin/in.tftpd\n"
"        server_args = -s /tftpboot\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:214
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now edit <path>/etc/xinetd.conf</path> and comment out the line <c>only_from =\n"
"localhost</c> by prefacing it with a <c>#</c>. Finally, start xinetd.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting xinetd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>rc-update add xinetd default</i>\n"
"# <i>/etc/init.d/xinetd start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:226
#, no-wrap
msgid "Name resolving"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:230
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In order for the workstation to reach all resources, a correct name\n"
"resolving must be available. There are several ways to achieve this. One\n"
"is to configure a DNS server for the local network, the other (and more\n"
"simple) is to have almost identical <path>/etc/hosts</path> files on all\n"
"systems. We are going to use the latter.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:238
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"All workstations must be listed in <path>/etc/hosts</path>. Take a look\n"
"at the example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:242
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/hosts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"127.0.0.1        localhost\n"
"192.168.0.254    server      server.yourdomain.com\n"
"192.168.0.1      ws001       ws001.yourdomain.com\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "DHCP Config"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is the most complicated step in my opinion, you have to create a\n"
"valid DHCP Config (<path>/etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf</path>). Here is an\n"
"example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:260
#, no-wrap
msgid "dhcpd.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:261
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Some general options)</comment>\n"
"default-lease-time            21600;\n"
"max-lease-time                21600;\n"
"use-host-decl-names           on;\n"
"ddns-update-style             ad-hoc;\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Bootp options)</comment>\n"
"allow booting;\n"
"allow bootp;\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Network Options)</comment>\n"
"option subnet-mask            255.255.255.0;\n"
"option broadcast-address      192.168.0.255;\n"
"option routers                192.168.0.254;\n"
"option domain-name-servers    192.168.0.254;\n"
"option log-servers            192.168.0.254;\n"
"option domain-name            \"yourdomain.com\";\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(LTSP Path Options)</comment>\n"
"option root-path              \"192.168.0.254:/opt/ltsp-4.1/i386\";\n"
"filename                      \"/lts/vmlinuz-2.4.26-ltsp-2\";\n"
"<comment>(Address of the tftp server to download the ltsp file from)</comment>\n"
"next-server                   192.168.0.254;\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(If your workstations have ISA NICs uncomment the following)</comment>\n"
"<comment>(lines and alter the driver and IO)</comment>\n"
"#option option-128 code 128 = string;\n"
"#option option-129 code 129 = text;\n"
"#option option-128 e4:45:74:68:00:00;\n"
"#option option-129 \"NIC=ne IO=0x300\";\n"
"\n"
"shared-network WORKSTATIONS {\n"
"  subnet 192.168.0.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {\n"
"    <comment>(Distribute dynamic IPs to the workstations)</comment>\n"
"    range dynamic-bootp 192.168.0.1 192.168.0.16;\n"
"    <comment>(Workstation specific configuration for PXE booting)</comment>\n"
"    #host ws001 {\n"
"    #  hardware ethernet     00:E0:06:E8:00:84;\n"
"    #  fixed-address         192.168.0.1;\n"
"    #}\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:306
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your workstations support PXE, you should list each one of them as we\n"
"have done with <e>host ws001</e> (don't forget to uncomment it). Don't\n"
"give them an adress in the dynamic range, otherwise it would be possible\n"
"that more workstations have the same IP (which is troublesome). Remember,\n"
"if you cut-n-paste the above example, replace any \"//\" comments with \"##\",\n"
"or else dhcp will fail to start.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:315
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For more documentation on this item read the official dhcp handbook:\n"
"<uri>http://www.dhcp-handbook.com/</uri>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:320
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now start DHCP as you did with NFS and xinetd:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "start dhcp"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:324
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>rc-update add dhcp default</i>\n"
"# <i>/etc/init.d/dhcp start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/ltsp.xml:329
#, no-wrap
msgid "DHCPD needs CONFIG_PACKET and CONFIG_FILTER activated in the kernel to work.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:335
#, no-wrap
msgid "LTSP Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:339
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are many options to configure your workstations, visit\n"
"<uri>http://ltsp.mirrors.tds.net/pub/ltsp/docs/ltsp-4.1-en.html#AEN1190</uri>\n"
"for a full description of <path>/opt/ltsp/i386/etc/lts.conf</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:345
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As a few suggestions to get started, you will want to first copy\n"
"<path>/opt/ltsp/i386/etc/lts.conf.example</path> to\n"
"<path>/opt/ltsp/i386/etc/lts.conf</path> and edit it from there. You may want\n"
"to try changing the <c>SCREEN_01</c> option to read <c>SCREEN_01 = startx</c>.\n"
"To use a USB mouse on the remote client, add the following MODULE lines, and\n"
"change the X_MOUSE_* lines as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:353
#, no-wrap
msgid "/opt/ltsp/i386/etc/lts.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"MODULE_01          = usb-uhci\n"
"MODULE_02          = mousedev\n"
"MODULE_03          = usbmouse\n"
"X_MOUSE_PROTOCOL   = \"IMPS/2\"\n"
"X_MOUSE_DEVICE     = \"/dev/input/mice\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/ltsp.xml:364
#, no-wrap
msgid "Displaymanager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:368
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now you have to change your displaymanager's configuration to\n"
"also accept remote connections.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:373
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First change your <path>/etc/X11/xdm/Xaccess</path> file,\n"
"uncomment the following line:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:377
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/X11/xdm/Xaccess"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:378
#, no-wrap
msgid "#*                   #any host can get a login window\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:382
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now change the configuration of the displaymanager you use:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:386
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>XDM</b>: In <path>/etc/X11/xdm/xdm-config</path> comment out\n"
"<c>DisplayManager.requestPort: 0</c>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:391
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>KDM</b>: In <path>/usr/kde/3.1/share/config/kdm/kdmrc</path> look\n"
"for the <c>[Xdmcp]</c> section and change <c>Enable = false</c> to\n"
"<c>Enable = true</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:397
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>GDM</b>: In <path>/etc/X11/gdm/gdm.conf</path> look for the\n"
"<c>[xdmcp]</c> section and change <c>Enable = false</c> to\n"
"<c>Enable = True</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/ltsp.xml:403
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then start the displaymanager:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:406
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting xdm"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/ltsp.xml:407
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>rc-update add xdm default</i>\n"
"# <i>/etc/init.d/xdm start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><warn>
#: en/ltsp.xml:412
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There seem to be problems currently with XDM and GDM. The author used\n"
